title.77: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #1

description.1: When Han and Chewie are forced to do battle in a gladiator arena, they'll find themselves locked in mortal combat.
description.2: Spencer Smythe and his Spider Slayers renew their pursuit of our favorite wall-crawler. J. Jonah Jameson makes an editorial goof that puts Spidey in even more danger! Will Spider-Man find an unexpected ally in his hour of greatest need?
description.3: The Avengers travel to the mystical city of The Bowery to acquire the stolen souls of Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch. But what is going on with the animate wooden dolls in birdcages? What happens in the Bowery, should stay in the Bowery!
description.4: Captain America finds himself going up a new kind of evil, when he and Peggy Carter set out to stop the Grand Director. Can Captain America triumph? Or will he get an old friend killed?
description.5: Our favorite Kree soldier takes on Chaos Himself! Drax the Destroyer guest-stars.
description.8: Daredevil and the Avengers attempt to fend off Death-Stalker, and the Ani-Men cause chaos!
description.9: Hulk lets Curtiss Jackson get away- but at the cost of saving another! Will Hulk join Marvel Man on his mission to re-capture Jackson?
description.10: Jerry and Spider-Woman are trapped in the twisted fairytale ""playhouse"" of Madam Doll!
description.11: Thor's mighty Mjolnir is trapped within the core of the planet Phantus! And the Space Phantom is at fault! There's only one way for Thor to retrieve his hammer- will he accept the risk involved?
description.12: Moses Magnum has issued an ultimatum to the government of Japan: Turn the country over to him, or he will use his Magnum Force to sink the entire country!
description.13: While the rest of the team is off trying to save the Andromeda Galaxy from menacing Skrulls, Johnny is back to school! Will hitting the books make or break the Human Torch?
description.18: Guest-starring Doctor Strange! The Thing uncovers a mystical hotspot while vacationing in an enchanted manor.
description.20: The ""Anything Man"" violently lashes out when the Defenders come to claim his power. Nighthawk takes a difficult beating.
description.21: Howard the Duck vs. Dr. Bong- the final battle is about to begin!
description.22: Despite misgivings, Spider-Man must save J. Jonah Jameson from the wrath of Man-Wolf! Will Jameson be able to talk sense into his now-lycanthropic son? Plus, a car show is crashed, but not in the way you think!
description.23: The First Appearance of Scott Lang, the man who would become Ant-Man!  Gyrich tells the Avengers they need to cut down to seven members, but with the way he's been running things there may not be any Avengers at all! Also, a strange man has nefarious plans for Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch!
description.24: Captain America sets out to find the Falcon once more, this time in his hometown, Harlem. But instead of finding his comrade, Cap finds the entire city hypnotized by the Grand Director, who has brought hatred, racism, and violence to New York City!
description.28: Dr. Sun and the Sphinx are now partners-in-crime! And Nova is forced to collect Powerhouse! Meanwhile, Comet is reunited with his son.
description.29: Vader finds a bounty hunter is also on the hunt for the person who destroyed the Death Star.  And Vader must get to this person first!
description.30: It's Ms. Marvel's biggest crisis yet - Carol Danvers is laid off from Woman Magazine!
description.32: Jack of Hearts meets with ""the Corporation"" to disastrous results.
description.35: Barbara Norriss reveals herself after duping the entire team as Valkyrie. Ollerus' army kicks into second gear.
description.36: Nathan Beame torments his father and Ghost Rider in a hellish display of power.
description.37: The Hulk is imprisoned at Alcatraz- alongside Captain America, Falcon, and Marvel Man! Can these four powerhouses break free from their bonds and save Jim Wilson?
description.38: While Iron Man fights a rogue SHIELD agent over Nick Fury's unconscious body, the helicarrier they are aboard drifts into Russian airspace.
description.39: Kristine is unwittingly swept up in cosmic battle when she's held as collateral in the Lunatik's Otherwar for Other Realm! Plus, who is the ""Stargod""?
description.40: Jessica and Jerry's night out is spoiled by the Brothers Grimm!
description.41: Thor brings Hyperion to Avengers Mansion to film a documentary, but the two are bombarded by a mystery assailant!
description.42: Without his powers, Dracula is a marked man!
description.44: When the X-Men arrive in Japan  they find that the city Agarashima is ablaze by a great firestorm caused by an unnatural earthquake
description.45: Reed is helping cure Willie Evans Jr. of a cosmic radiation coma- but is it the boy's father who's the real problem? Can the team defeat Evan Sr.'s FF doppelg'ngers and cure his mutant son?
description.51: Will a televised "attack" on civilians by the Rebels discredit the whole Rebellion and cause many to leave their cause?
description.52: The mystery of John Jameson's disappearance continues to unfold when Spider-Man intercepts a plutonium robbery. Peter must make difficult decisions when it comes to Aunt May's health. Plus, Spider-Man gets in trouble with the NYPD!
description.53: The Avengers visit the mystical island of Muara to return a religious artifact. Little do they know, the island is protected by a monolithic stone creature out for blood!
description.54: Captain America teams up with Marvel Man and Vamp to infiltrate the Alcatraz Corporation, but things go haywire when Bruce Banner is abducted! Plus: Who's working with Kligger?
description.58: This space-scraping series takes an earthbound turn- what extraterrestrial activity has been occurring in Kentucky?
description.61: A comatose Daredevil must fight for his life against?himself?
description.62: The story starts with a bang as the Fantastic Four chase down the Sandman to stop a bank robbery! Afterwards, Reed, Sue, Ben, and Johnny return to the Baxter Building and agree to take a vacation to Colorado with Agatha Harkness. A vacation to the Rocky Mountains sounds great, but perhaps somewhere besides New Salem! Unbeknownst to the fabulous foursome, the Salem Seven are lying in wait to ambush them! And then steal the FF's powers to bring Nicholas Scratch back to Earth's realm! Back in New York City, the cataclysmic confrontation takes place: Agatha Harkness and young Franklin vs. Nicholas Scratch and the Salem Seven! Cameo appearances by Captain America, Captain Marvel, Falcon, Iron Man, Ms. Marvel, Nighthawk, Vision, Wonder Man, and Peter Parker.
description.63: The Hulk is tricked into making friends, as Jim Wilson is tricked into finding the Hulk. With both bamboozled, what will become of the Gamma Base?
description.64: First Appearance of James "Rhodey" Rhodes, a.k.a War Machine. After being knocked unconscious by rogue S.H.I.E.L.D. agents, Tony is thrown out of a Helicarrier hangar bay and plummets toward certain doom.  Can Iron Man save himself and expose the traitorous agents?
description.65: A romantic beach tryst with Jerry is interrupted by the arrival of a flying woman! Enter the Gypsy Moth!
description.66: Pluto and Loki have kidnapped Jane Foster! And Thor must battle Ulik to recover her!
description.67: Following their departure from the Savage Land, the X-Men find themselves caught in the middle of a terrible storm at sea.
description.68: The Fantastic Four join forces with Iron Man to find out who hijacked their HQ and Tony Stark's Iron Man design. And the hunt for answers leads to some startling revelations!
description.71: Under pressure from his criminal lackeys, Jigsaw organizes a heist that will draw out costumed super heroes. A night out for Peter Parker and friends turns into a high-crime adventure when Liz Allan and Harry Osborn are captured by Jigsaw! Will Peter be able to save those he holds dear, and protect his identity as Spider-Man?
description.72: While hosting a charity benefit at the Museum of Natural History, the Avengers encounter Bloodhawk. The avian villain makes off with a rare artifact from the island of Muara. How will the Avengers return the Muara Totem to its rightful exhibit? And why did Bloodhawk need the totem in the first place?
description.73: Captain America sets out to find the Falcon, but his journey soon becomes complicated when a mysterious corporation is revealed! Will Cap ever find Sam Wilson?
description.74: On the gambler's paradise known as The Wheel, Han enters a gladiator contest known as The Big Game!
description.75: While Luke Skywalker and Princess Leia are on the planet Tirahnn they are attacked by a group of Catuman warriors under the orders of Kharys, the Majestrix of Skye. Plus, Han Solo gets shot down!
description.83: The Thing suspects foul play on Yancy Street, and it's all but confirmed once the Yancy Street Gang leaves their calling card!
description.86: Valkyrie finds herself a prisoner in a mystically-bound jail! But who is her captive? The Defenders charge Valhalla to eliminate Hela and her undead army.
description.87: Back in Cleveland, Howard is again contemplating life decisions he has made. Joey, a good friend of Howard's, comes up with a plan to make money in Las Vegas. You wouldn't believe what happens next.
description.88: Dr. Sun captures Nova to fulfill his plan of taking control of the Nova Prime ship. But is this really a cure for immortality? But Dr. Sun isn't the only one with Nova in his plans…
description.89: Captives of the Lizard People! The reptilian ruler refuses to release Carol and her friends, for fear of them revealing the Lizards to the human race!
description.90: Attack of the Master Mold! Doc Samson must defend mutants Angel and Iceman from the Mega-Sentinel. But where is the Hulk in this frenzy of a fight?
description.95: Before Valkyrie can embrace her future, she must put Barbara Norriss to rest. But at the cost of her powers? An Asgardian adventure in the Reign Eternal!
description.96: Ebenezer Scrooge learns the lesson of his lifetime on a haunted Christmas Eve. Adapting Charles Dickens' holiday classic A Christmas Carol!
description.97: For the sake of a pay raise, Peter infiltrates Indian Point, an abandoned town quarantined by S.H.I.E.L.D. Will Spider-Man uncover the secrets of Indian Point before another citizen falls at the hands of Electro? Plus, Spider-Man does battle with Captain America!
description.98: While picking up women in a nightclub, Beast is assaulted by an anti-mutant fanatic. On his way home, he encounters a mysterious ghost telling him to be "absolved of all anger." Who is this apparition visiting Beast? And who is the mysterious woman demanding a favor from the Beast?
description.99: Captain America and the Constrictor! Can Cap defeat this new villain? Plus: Where's Sam Wilson, the Falcon?

0.text: Power Man and Iron Fist are hired to protect an exhibit of ancient Egyptian artifacts at the Metropolitan Museum. During the night, a robbery orchestrated by a dangerous villain goes down! Power Man and Iron Fist follow their lead to solve this crime, only to discover that the Living Monolith is the true mastermind!

5.text: Our favorite Kree soldier takes on Chaos Himself! Drax the Destroyer guest-stars.

6.text: The Invaders take on Lady Lotus and U-Man!

7.text: DEMON IN A BOTTLE PART 1 One of Tony Stark's closest allies has betrayed him. After many fierce battles, the Golden Avenger is exhausted and ready to give up. But when Sub-Mariner comes looking for a fight, will Iron Man be able to face him?

8.text: Daredevil and the Avengers attempt to fend off Death-Stalker, and the Ani-Men cause chaos!

14.text: As Spider-Man tries to stop the Masked Marauder's Tri-Man robot, Daredevil faces off alone against the Marauder and his goons.

17.text: The Black Panther in the Big Apple! T'Challa faces down a local gang of looters, but they have a secret weapon -- one that T'Challa knows extremely well!

25.text: Shang-Chi finds himself in an uneasy alliance with Shockwave when both of their lives come under danger on Mordillo Isle!

28.text: Dr. Sun and the Sphinx are now partners-in-crime! And Nova is forced to collect Powerhouse! Meanwhile, Comet is reunited with his son.

30.text: It's Ms. Marvel's biggest crisis yet - Carol Danvers is laid off from Woman Magazine!

31.text: The final showdown between the Invaders and the Iron Cross! Plus, the return of U-Man and the debut of Lady Lotus.

34.text: Dream Weaver visits the Sanctum Santorum in an attempt to steal Doctor Strange's Book of Vishanti!

46.text: Daredevil tries to help Spider-Man cope and be able to get by with his newfound blindness.

47.text: Return to Mordillo Isle! Shang-Chi and Leiko battle some monstrous mutations on the island that time forgot!

50.text: TO SLEEP, PERCHANCE TO DIE Star-Lord encounters a lost civilization of two billion people roaming the cosmos in a extraordinary ark.

55.text: Bull, a criminal who once fought the likes of Captain America, goes to a local car show with one thing on his mind: stealing the on-display Fantasti-car! Power Man and Iron Fist try to stop this raging villain, but unfortunately Bull brought back-up!

57.text: The Invaders step up to the plate when the Liberty Legion is downed by the Iron Cross.

58.text: This space-scraping series takes an earthbound turn- what extraterrestrial activity has been occurring in Kentucky?

59.text: While the Avengers meet to discuss Arsenal, Beast and Hawkeye uncover a secret beneath Avengers Mansion...one that dates back to World War II! What is Project Tomorrow, and how is it connected to Tony Stark's legacy?

61.text: A comatose Daredevil must fight for his life against…himself?

69.text: Spider-Man…blinded! How will the wall-crawler protect New York without his sight? Sounds like a question for DAREDEVIL, Man Without Fear!

77.text: Continuing from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN ANNUAL #13! Will Spider-Man finally defeat Doctor Octopus?

78.text: The villainous Shockwave begins targeting Shang-Chi’s friends! But to what end?

80.text: Thor vs. Zeus in a thunderous battle at the heart of Olympus!

81.text: Witness the return of DOCTOR OCTOPUS! Get ready for an action-packed (and strange) Spidey story when the web-slinger comes face-to-face once more with one of his greatest enemies!

84.text: Spider-Man and Ms. Marvel join forces to stop the Witch-Queen of New Orleans from taking over Doctor Strange's astral form!

88.text: Dr. Sun captures Nova to fulfill his plan of taking control of the Nova Prime ship. But is this really a cure for immortality? But Dr. Sun isn't the only one with Nova in his plans…

89.text: Captives of the Lizard People! The reptilian ruler refuses to release Carol and her friends, for fear of them revealing the Lizards to the human race!

90.text: Attack of the Master Mold! Doc Samson must defend mutants Angel and Iceman from the Mega-Sentinel. But where is the Hulk in this frenzy of a fight?

91.text: The Whizzer has a secret that could help the Allies win the war, but he refuses to reveal it. And so the Invaders must catch a man who can’t be caught.

92.text: It’s a battle of brawn between the Ever-Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing and the Incredible Hulk! Which of these beloved heroes will come out on top in this fierce battle?

93.text: A bizarre orb unleashes a demon in Doctor Strange's Sanctum. But with Strange's powers on the fritz and Clea's soul removed from her body, the Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man must take the case!

94.text: The birth of DREAM WEAVER! The supernatural villainess tampers with an ancient spell, prompting chaos for Strange and Clea.
